Description: use x-terminal-emulator instead of xterm
 x-terminal-emulator is a sensible default terminal emulator on Debian, so
 use it instead of xterm in the default configuration.
Forwarded: not-needed
Author: Andrea Bolognani <eof@kiyuko.org>
Last-Update: 2014-08-17
Index: spectrwm.git/spectrwm.1
===================================================================
--- spectrwm.git.orig/spectrwm.1	2014-08-17 21:47:21.000000000 +0200
+++ spectrwm.git/spectrwm.1	2014-08-17 21:49:15.328036666 +0200
@@ -497,7 +497,7 @@
 dmenu_run $dmenu_bottom \-fn $bar_font \-nb $bar_color \-nf $bar_font_color \-sb
 $bar_border \-sf $bar_color
 .It Cm term
-xterm
+x-terminal-emulator
 .It Cm initscr
 initscreen.sh        # optional
 .It Cm screenshot_all
